parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The "death wobble" can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: the front end of the truck oscillates
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control
often requiring the driver to slow down to regain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and violent shaking of the front end of the vehicle, known as the "death wobble," can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Violent shaking of the steering column
or front end of the vehicle at highway speeds
often triggered by hitting a bump or rough patch in the road; difficulty controlling the vehicle; shaking may persist until the vehicle is slowed down to a low speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failure can cause the engine to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
DPF failure can cause the engine to lose power, overheat, and potentially catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
EGT sensor failure can cause the engine to shut down while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
High pressure fuel pump failure can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Clutch and hydraulic system failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.
